2/ Use the fastai library Give it shot today with @FloydHub_ 's latest @PyTorch -1.0 environment https://twitter.com/FloydHub_/status/1058425299937853440/photo/1 pic.twitter.com/EeME7YfMNT pic.twitter.com/AqNK7QuAbB
12/ Dig into more @fastdotai techniques with @SamLynnEvans 's post on the @FloydHub_ blog: https:// blog.floydhub.com/ten-techniques -from-fast-ai/ …
11/ Creativity is key Data science can only get you so far -- and it's best combined your unique domain knowledge and expertise! pic.twitter.com/0mjmKrESL2

10/ Building up sizes, dropout, and test time automation Use dropout to combat overfitting, which #fastai does automatically for you in its learn objects. These techniques can help boost your model accuracy.

9/ #DeepLearning is starting to get better at tackling structured data The #fastai library can leverage @pytorch 's embedding functions instead of traditional #MachineLearning approaches (e.g. one-hot-encoding) for structured data
8/ Transfer learning is hugely effective in NLP pic.twitter.com/Q8xSFcYknH

7/ Anthropomorphize your activation functions Softmax likes to pick one thing. Sigmoid wants to know where you are between -1 and 1. Relu is like a bouncer who won't let negative numbers through the door. It may seem silly, but it helps

6/ SGD with restarts SGDR helps you avoid getting stuck in a local minima by reseting your learning rate at the start of each epoch. This is handled for you automatically by #fastai ! pic.twitter.com/BgIYmTKoaK
5/ Cosine annealing #fastai 's http:// learn.fit automatically takes advantage of cosine annealing to decrease the learning rate over time pic.twitter.com/bCfZ9T5TIS
4/ They try to find the right learning rate The fastai library comes with a learning rate finder built-in! pic.twitter.com/qJMUB6QaiQ
3/ Don't use one learning rate, they use many pic.twitter.com/5jbmYoqq76
